text: 23-4 Scoped and ranged the station to minimize PHJ...Wait watch att, But looks good

title: FACET Q2E
text: Q2E Went to take look at EMHP and found it is once again out of regulation at 2KW. Checked the TB3 4 and 6 connection and found them to be snug, Also checked the Xductor cables on back of controller chassis and found ok. Probbem either the error card or worst of the Xductor mods, ACR didn't want to chance trim att in the event it might interfere with their beam...OBTW

title: Investigating loss of transmission
SHOP
text: Checked out the 237-212 controller chassis from the EMHP test stand it seems to be ok think there might be a bad cable, Will check to see when SSA tests are completed, As I didn't want to turn off the supply in the event they are recording test data.

title: Gallery
text: Did another search for a spare choke for the supply that has a bad choke for the 'B" phase could not locate one, All the chokes under the table in test area are marked shorted and need to be salvaged.

title: Request from FACET folks to take data for ~15 min
text: S. Gessner would like to take data for a short amount of time while we are at -20 chirp. He doesn't need to change anything, just insert and remove a couple of screens. We will work on tuning up the beam and then turn it over when we're ready.

text: HPS fault dumped beam (need to get details from DO, D. Day). Refilled/delivered 500mA. Down 23 minutes.

FACET summary so far
text: took bunch length measurements at -5, -10, and -15 L2 Chirp each of the chirp settings has a config saved in score and SCP each of the scores is >80% transmission to the dump CONFIG 6133 has no label for chirp but it is at -5 L2 Chirp Program called for emittance scans in sector 19 i forgot to do these i would recommend doing them when scanning down from maximum chirp settings

title: Beam back down machine
Second walkthrough complete, no issues found.
text: Prep in MFX, beam going to XCS.

title: Shift summary: Sunday swing
text: SUMMARY: HPS fault dumped beam. Refilled/delivered 500mA; down 23 minutes. INJECTOR: Autofill, average fill rate 52mA/min, 97% injection efficiency. SPEAR: 500mA stored beam with top-off fills every 5 minutes except during beam lost. HPS fault dumped beam at 18:44. It was BL15 Fast valve Logic fault according to Duty Operator. Refilled/delivered 500mA at 19:07.

title: SWING SHIFT SUMMARY
text:
Comment # Comment 1LCLS: Delivered 6keV (8.3GeV) to CXI, 2.1mJ. 2LCLS: Delivered 8keV (9.65GeV) to XCS, 1.9mJ. 3FACET-II: Did beam length measurement at -5 L2 Chirp. Then improved transmission and did beam length measurements at -10 and -15 L2 Chirp setpoints. 4FACET-II: FACET team opportunistically took data while we were at -20 L2 Chirp setpoint for ~15 min.

text: Desc: BSOLNW12 has faulted and will not reset after pulling power at the BSOIC, in S10 adit. Installed jumper at the S08 BSO PLC J1 (first input) to clear fault. We have seen this symptom before with other SC LINAC BSOICS. once we plug the power back into the BSOIC (yellow connector) we get a fault on our PLC and we cannot reset. Installed jumper at BSO PLC (in S08) and the fault went away, we were able to reset. must be replaced. And this problem should be understood before moving forward. This has happened to several SC LINAC gamma BSOICs. RP replaces BSOICS but the cause of the problem MUST be investigated. Reqs: All Linac West SSAs 480 VAC is locked off by ADSO.
